==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pan-Anglican
<hw>Pan`-An"gli*can</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pan-</ets> + <ets>Anglican</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld>
<def>Belonging to, or representing, the whole Church of England; used
less strictly, to include the Protestant Episcopal Church of the United
States; <as>as, the <ex>Pan-Anglican</ex> Conference at Lambeth, in
1888</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Panary</ent>⟦br⟧
